lized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9956446886062622, "span": {"begin": 531, "end": 543}}, {"id": ["mesh:D003687"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DHEA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9977614879608154, "span": {"begin": 610, "end": 614}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9698758125305176, "span": {"begin": 624, "end": 636}}], "text": "Exposure to stressors can lead to a decrease of DHEA that in turn leads to decrease of downstream hormones like testosterone.&nbsp;  Using H295R cells, exposure of ketoconazole resulted in a dose-dependent decreased in the levels of DHEA and testosterone (Nielsen et al., 2012). This was also observed using fluconazole on both H295R cells and its clonal cell line, HAC15 (van der Pas et al., 2012).&nbsp;  In female individuals with decreased libido, reduced levels of DHEA-sulfate, which represents a reservoir pool of DHEA, and testosterone have been observed (Guay et al., 2002). Oral supplementation with DHEA restores testosterone levels (Li etal., 2020; Liu et al., 2013).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:16:52 +0000 2026"}